The following post uses an Engage tactic by bringing up a related but relevant topic:

@Azoria_J I hope they can shop season 2 & 3 around. I'm really, really hoping it's like with the Sandman, Gaiman always said that if Shitflix were to cancel it, He could always shop it around. So I'm strongly hoping that it is something they can do with 1899 as well 😅

This tweet brings up the idea of shopping a show around to other platforms, similar to what happened with another show, "Sandman." It engages with the topic of finding alternative ways to continue a show that has been canceled by a streaming platform.
